    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Key insight:** The salary distribution is concentrated mostly below $200,000, with the highest density around the middle salary range and a long right tail extending toward higher compensation levels. This indicates that most job postings fall within a typical salary band, but a smaller number of high-paying postings create substantial variation. Because of this skewed distribution, later salary analysis should evaluate both average prediction error and the effect of high-salary outliers rather than relying only on central tendency.\n",
        "\n",
        "## 6. Salary Distribution by Job Characteristics\n",
        "\n",
        "Why this visualization was chosen:  \n",
        "This section explores whether salary differs across important job characteristics such as  education level, and occupation. These comparisons help identify which variables appear meaningful for later salary analysis."
      ],
      "id": "3265259d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "message": false
      },
      "source": [
        "#| echo: fenced\n",
        "#| code-fold: true\n",
        "#| code-summary: Show code\n",
        "#| warning: false\n",
        "\n",
        "education_salary = spark.sql(\"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT\n",
        "    CASE\n",
        "        WHEN LOWER(COALESCE(e.education_level, 'Unknown')) LIKE '%ph.d%' THEN 'PhD / Professional'\n",
        "        WHEN LOWER(COALESCE(e.education_level, 'Unknown')) LIKE '%professional degree%' THEN 'PhD / Professional'\n",
        "        WHEN LOWER(COALESCE(e.education_level, 'Unknown')) LIKE '%master%' THEN 'Master'\n",
        "        WHEN LOWER(COALESCE(e.education_level, 'Unknown')) LIKE '%bachelor%' THEN 'Bachelor'\n",
        "        WHEN LOWER(COALESCE(e.education_level, 'Unknown')) LIKE '%associate%' THEN 'Associate'\n",
        "        WHEN LOWER(COALESCE(e.education_level, 'Unknown')) LIKE '%high school%' THEN 'High School / GED'\n",
        "        ELSE 'Unknown'\n",
        "    END AS education_level_clean,\n",
        "    j.salary\n",
        "FROM job_postings j\n",
        "LEFT JOIN education_levels e\n",
        "    ON j.id = e.id\n",
        "WHERE j.salary IS NOT NULL\n",
        "  AND j.salary > 0\n",
        "  AND j.salary <= 500000\n",
        "\"\"\").toPandas()\n",
        "\n",
        "education_order = [\n",
        "    \"High School / GED\",\n",
        "    \"Associate\",\n",
        "    \"Bachelor\",\n",
        "    \"Master\",\n",
        "    \"PhD / Professional\",\n",
        "    \"Unknown\"\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "fig_education_salary = px.box(\n",
        "    education_salary,\n",
        "    x=\"education_level_clean\",\n",
        "    y=\"salary\",\n",
        "    color=\"education_level_clean\",\n",
        "    category_orders={\"education_level_clean\": education_order},\n",
        "    title=\"Salary Distribution by Education Level\",\n",
        "    labels={\n",
        "        \"education_level_clean\": \"Education Level\",\n",
        "        \"salary\": \"Salary ($)\"\n",
        "    },\n",
        "    color_discrete_sequence=px.colors.qualitative.Set3\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "fig_education_salary.update_layout(\n",
        "    template=\"plotly_white\",\n",
        "    height=480,\n",
        "    margin=dict(l=60, r=40, t=70, b=90),\n",
        "    title=dict(x=0.02, xanchor=\"left\"),\n",
        "    showlegend=False,\n",
        "    xaxis_tickangle=-25,\n",
        "    yaxis=dict(tickprefix=\"$\", separatethousands=True)\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "fig_education_salary.show()"
